odel as a conceptual basis for net decomposition kinetics. Early diagenetic fractionation of C isotopes relative to the bulk sedimentary Corgcomposition can produce changes in14C activity independent of radioactive decay. In the Gulf of Papua topset-upper foreset, $\Delta$14C of pore water $\Sigma$CO2averaged ∼ 300‰ greater than Corgsediment between ∼1-3 m depth in deposits. Diagenetic fractionation and decomposition aging of sedimentary Corgcompromises simple application of14C for determination of sediment accumulation rates in diagenetically reactive deposits. {\textcopyright} 2004 Elsevier Ltd.},
