es), perhaps by causing the dissociation of gas hydrates. The variable efficiency of global carbon sinks during volcanic episodes may be an important control on environmental effects and may explain why the eruption of some vast igneousprovinces, such as the Paran{\'{a}}Etendeka Traps, have little perceptible climatic impact.},
