acetate as an electron donor under Fe(III)-reducing conditions. In sum-mary, this study shows that increasing concentrations of OM in OM–mineral complexes determines microbial Fe(III) re-duction rates and shapes the microbial community structure involved in the reductive dissolution of ferrihydrite. Simi-larities observed between the complex Fe(III)-reducing mi-crobial consortia and the model Fe(III)-reducer S. oneiden-sis MR-1 suggest electron-shuttling mechanisms dominate in OM-rich environments, including soils, sediments, and fens, where natural OM interacts with Fe(III) oxides during min-eral formation.},
