al isolation of sufficient pollen from the fossil record for $\delta$13C analysis of a single species would be prohibitively laborious; however, these results showed that when understood in terms of paleobotanical taxonomy, $\delta$13C analyses of bulk fossil pollen can be used to infer the $\delta$13C value of the ancient plant community to within 1.5‰. {\textcopyright} 2004 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.},
