y in northwestern Europe, were often restricted to relatively shallow water over tectonically controlled topographic highs. Evolution of new organisms during mid-Carboniferous time led to a diversification of buildup types. However, microbial fabrics identical to those developed in Dinantian buildups are still present in many late Carboniferous and Permian phylloid algal, Palaeoaplysina and bryozoan buildups. The role of microbial activity in the development of these late Carboniferous and Permian buildups may have been greatly underestimated.},
