bian Sea. Present-day conditions in the Makran area were established at 1500 yr BP (Period V). Based on inorganic geochemical data and meteorological records at several stations in the Makran we conclude that Period V is dominated by precipitation during the winter season. Here, declined rainfall associated with the summer-monsoon may be related to a less northward position of the intertropical convergence zone (ITCZ) during summer and a stronger in¯uence of winter-monsoon linked phenomenona.},
