m. This, together with the fact at that both the Emeishan basalts and the Chaotian clay rest on the Maokou Formation, leads us to infer that the Emeishan basalt was emplaced at the Middle-Late Permian boundary. In this sense, the Emeishan volcanism can be regarded as a boundary event and its age is presumed at ?????260??Ma. Although more precise dating is required, both stratigraphic correlation and chronologic data presented in this paper lend supports to the notion that the Emeishan volcanism was one of likely causes of the end-Guadalupian mass extinction. ?? 2007 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.},
